<task id="AIPU2-121" project="Spaarke AI Platform Unification R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Deploy BFF API with all new R2 services</title>
    <phase>7</phase>
    <tags>deploy, bff-api</tags>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-effort>3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>AIPU2-120</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    Deploy the updated BFF API to the dev App Service with all R2 services active: capability
    router, safety pipeline, session persistence (Cosmos), conversation history, audit logging,
    and feedback collection. This is a standard deploy via Deploy-BffApi.ps1. After deployment,
    verify that the health check passes, new endpoints respond correctly, and the safety services
    (Azure Content Safety, groundedness check) connect successfully. Cosmos DB must be deployed
    first (AIPU2-120).
  </prompt>
  <role>DevOps engineer following the bff-deploy skill procedure.</role>
  <goal>
    BFF API is deployed to spe-api-dev-67e2xz with all R2 services operational. Health check
    returns 200. New R2 endpoints (/api/session, /api/audit, /api/feedback, /api/ai/route)
    respond correctly. Safety services connect to Azure Content Safety API. No regressions
    on existing R1 endpoints.
  </goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>scripts/Deploy-BffApi.ps1</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/bff-deploy/SKILL.md</file>
      <file>docs/guides/AI-DEPLOYMENT-GUIDE.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Program.cs</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Load the bff-deploy skill and follow its pre-deployment checklist: verify all R2 tests pass (dotnet test), verify no pending migrations, confirm appsettings are updated with Cosmos DB endpoint and container names from AIPU2-120.</step>
    <step>Run dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ in Release configuration and confirm build succeeds with no errors or warnings.</step>
    <step>Run dotnet publish to produce the deployment artifact. Verify the publish output includes all new R2 service assemblies.</step>
    <step>Execute scripts/Deploy-BffApi.ps1 targeting the dev environment (spe-api-dev-67e2xz). Monitor deployment progress and capture output log.</step>
    <step>Verify health check: GET https://spe-api-dev-67e2xz.azurewebsites.net/healthz returns 200 OK with all components healthy (including new Cosmos DB health probe).</step>
    <step>Verify new R2 endpoints: (a) POST /api/session/create returns 201; (b) GET /api/ai/route with a simple message returns a routing decision; (c) POST /api/feedback returns 200; (d) GET /api/audit/recent returns audit entries.</step>
    <step>Verify safety service connectivity: check Application Insights or logs for successful Azure Content Safety API handshake. Confirm no authentication errors for safety service Managed Identity access.</step>
    <step>Run a smoke test of existing R1 endpoints: document search, file operations, etc. Confirm no regressions.</step>
    <step>Record deployment details in notes/deploy-bff-api-log.md: deployment time, version, endpoint verification results.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>BFF API deploys successfully to spe-api-dev-67e2xz with no deployment errors.</criterion>
    <criterion>GET /healthz returns 200 with all components healthy including Cosmos DB.</criterion>
    <criterion>All four new R2 endpoints respond correctly (session, routing, feedback, audit).</criterion>
    <criterion>Safety services connect successfully to Azure Content Safety API — no authentication errors.</criterion>
    <criterion>Existing R1 endpoints continue to work — no regressions detected in smoke test.</criterion>
    <criterion>Deployment log written to notes/deploy-bff-api-log.md.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
